PART 1 — Introduction to Hashing


---

Define

Hashing converts data into a fixed-size output.

Example:

HELLO
↓
Hash
↓
3733cd977ff...


---

Important Property

Same input:

HELLO

Always gives:

3733cd977ff...


---

Change one character:

HELLo

Produces a completely different hash.


---

Why Is This Useful?

Suppose:

Customer transfers:

₹10,000

Hash generated.


---

Attacker changes:

₹100,000

Hash changes.

Integrity violation detected.


---

Banking Example

Passwords.

Bank should NEVER store:

Password123

Instead:

Password123
↓
Hash
↓
Store Hash


---

Validate

Question:

Can hashes be decrypted?

NO.

Hashing is one-way.


