PART 2 — SHA-1


---

Define

SHA = Secure Hash Algorithm

SHA-1 was once widely trusted.


---

Purpose

Generate unique fingerprints for data.


---

Example:

File
↓
SHA-1 Hash


---

Problem

Researchers found:

Collisions


---

Collision

Two different inputs produce same hash.


---

Example:

File A
↓
Hash X

File B
↓
Hash X

Dangerous.


---

Why It Matters

Hashes are used to verify integrity.

If collisions exist:

Trust decreases.


---

Security Lesson

Algorithms don't become bad overnight.

Computers improve.

Attack methods improve.


---

Banking Application

Most modern systems avoid SHA-1 for security-sensitive uses.


---

