PART 4 — Rainbow Tables

This is a favorite interview topic.


---

Problem

Imagine attacker steals:

Password Hashes

Good news:

No plaintext passwords.


---

Bad news:

Attackers can still attempt recovery.


---

What Is A Rainbow Table?

A giant precomputed database.

Example:

Hash
↓
Original Password


---

Example:

5f4dcc3b5aa...
↓
password


---

Instead of guessing passwords one by one:

Attackers look them up.

Much faster.


---

Banking Example

Database breach.

Attacker obtains:

Username
Hash

Rainbow tables help crack weak passwords.


---

Defense: Salting

Most important concept.


---

What Is A Salt?

Random value added before hashing.


---

Example:

Without Salt

Password123
↓
Hash

Same password.

Same hash.


---

With Salt

Password123
+
Random Salt
↓
Hash

Different users get different hashes.


---

Result

Rainbow tables become ineffective.


---

Why Banks Use Salting

Protect customer credentials.

Reduce effectiveness of database breaches.


